Module HunterPaceTimes
Package Classes

Class Pace

java.lang.Object
Classes.Pace
public class Pace
extends java.lang.Object
An object containing all data of a given pace. This class contains the list of divisions and teams currently in the pace. Whenever this object is saved or loaded from a file, it uses the Json tool to convert it to JSON.

    • updateDivisions

      public void updateDivisions()
      Updates the division list, removing old divisions and adding new ones according to the teams list

      First goes through and identifies any new divisions, and counts the uses for each of the current divisions.

      Then, it marks each division with the following conditions for deletion

      • No current Team teams in the list have this division
      • The division has no goal time set. This is to prevent deletion of manually coded divisions

      After identifying divisions to remove and add, it removes each division marked for deletion, and adds all new divisions with no goal time

    • getPlaces

      public Team[] getPlaces​(Division division)
      Returns the places of a specific division
      Parameters:
      division - Specific Division to return the places for
      Returns:
      Team array of all teams in that division, in order of closeness to the goal time

      Returns Null if division is null, if it cannot be found in the current list of divisions, or if the division does not have a goal time.
      This method will excluded any teams marked with the excluded from final scores tab

    • getPlaces

      public Team[] getPlaces​(Division division, boolean includeExcluded)
      Returns the places of a specific division
      Parameters:
      division - Specific Division to return the places for
      includeExcluded - Whether or not to include teams marked with the excluded from scores identifier. If this is set to true, only teams that are not included (by default for new teams) will be added to the places. If set to false, then all teams, regardless of their exclusion tag, will be included in the scores
      Returns:
      Team array of all teams in that division, in order of closeness to the goal time

      Returns Null if division is null, if it cannot be found in the current list of divisions, or if the division does not have a goal time.
